  <h2><a href="/articles/2011/03/22/interview-on-the-change-log-show/">Change Log Show Interview</a></h2>
  <p class="info">by <a href="/about/">John W. Long</a> on March 22, 2011</p>
  <p><img src="/page_attachments/0000/0118/changelog.png" /></p>

<p>A couple of weeks ago I sat down with <a href="http://adamstacoviak.com/">Adam Stacoviack</a>, co-host of <em><a href="http://thechangelog.com">The Change Log Show</a></em>  to talk about:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="http://radiantcms.org">Radiant <span class="caps">CMS</span></a> &#8211; a content management system I created</li>
  <li><a href="http://github.com/jlong/serve">Serve</a> &#8211; a rapid prototyping framework for web apps</li>
  <li><a href="http://github.com/jlong/acoustic">Acoustic</a> &#8211; a small web framework I&#8217;m building in my spare time</li>
  <li><a href="http://wiseheartdesign.com/articles/2010/02/17/open-source-design-help-needed/">Design and open source</a></li>
  <li>My work on the <a href="http://rubyidentity.org">Ruby Visual Identity Team</a></li>
  <li>And many other unusual and tantalizing things</li>
</ul>

<p>The interview is now posted on the show&#8217;s website. If you are new to my work, you will definitely enjoy listening along as we explore the many different facets of my career and my love for software development.</p>

<p><em>The Change Log Show</em> is a weekly podcast and blog that covers what&#8217;s fresh and new in Open Source.</p>

<p><a href="http://thechangelog.com/post/3904430915/episode-0-5-2-serve-radiantcms-prototyping-and-design-wi" class="more">Listen to the Podcast</a></p>
  
