  <h2><a href="/articles/2011/01/13/design-experiments-css3-compass-and-radiant/">Design Experiments: CSS3, Compass, and Radiant</a></h2>
  <p class="info">by <a href="/about/">John W. Long</a> on January 13, 2011</p>
  <p><a href="/articles/2011/01/13/design-experiments-css3-compass-and-radiant/"><img src="/page_attachments/0000/0114/brace.png" /></a></p>

<p>Here&#8217;s a little teaser image from some work that I&#8217;ve been doing rewriting the stylesheets of Radiant <span class="caps">CMS</span>. I&#8217;ve removed almost all of the background images in favor of CSS3 gradients and am working on a couple of other improvements.</p>

<p>One of the things that I&#8217;m playing around with is a new style for the second navigation row. This should allow us to put common actions on the toolbar like a &#8220;New Page&#8221; button.</p>

<p>For now, these changes are in an <a href="https://github.com/radiant/radiant-prototype/tree/brace">experimental branch</a> of the Radiant <span class="caps">CMS</span> prototype project. Check out <a href="https://github.com/radiant/radiant-prototype/compare/master...brace">the compare</a> to see how CSS3 and Compass are making Radiant better.</p>
  
</div>

<div class="post">
  <h2><a href="/articles/2010/11/12/the-designers-guide-to-the-osx-command-prompt/">The Designer’s Guide to the OSX Command Prompt</a></h2>
  <p class="info">by <a href="/about/">John W. Long</a> on November 12, 2010</p>
  <p>The command prompt. Once the lofty domain of <em>that guy you know</em> with the computer science degree. Now more and more the every day domain of the <em><a href="http://twitter.com/zeldman/status/4818978868">hacker web designer</a></em>.</p>

<p>Perhaps you&#8217;ve mastered a little Javascript or PHP, but you are realizing that the cool kids are playing around with stuff that is only accessible to people who are comfortable with the command prompt. Or, perhaps you are just interested in upping your game.</p>

<p>Whatever the case, I&#8217;m here to help. In this brief introduction I&#8217;ll give you a small tour of command prompt on <span class="caps">OSX</span>. We&#8217;re only going to scratch the surface, but hopefully you&#8217;ll walk away with enough knowledge to get you started. With just a little know-how you&#8217;ll be hopping around the command prompt typing out shell incantations like a pro.</p>
  <p class="more"><a href="/articles/2010/11/12/the-designers-guide-to-the-osx-command-prompt/#extended">Continue Reading</a></p>
</div>

